        <updateDate>2017-03-31T20:54:01Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>End of Debtors Prison Act of 2017</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Omnibus Crime Control and Safe Streets Act of 1968 to prohibit the Department of Justice from allocating Edward Byrne Memorial Justice Assistance Grant program funding to a state or local government that has a contract with a person (e.g., a private probation company) who: (1) collects unpaid debt (i.e., state- or court-imposed fines or fees) from an individual placed on probation for failing to pay such debt; and (2) charges separate fees (e.g., monthly fees) to the probationer with respect to the collection. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>End of Debtors Prison Act of 2017</title>
